      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/31/4",
      "text": [
        ": «كَانَ رَسُولُ اَللَّهِ صَلَّى اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ آلِهِ إِذَا دَخَلَ اَلْعَشْرُ اَلْأَوَاخِرُ شَدَّ اَلْمِئْزَرَ وَ اِجْتَنَبَ اَلنِّسَاءَ وَ أَحْيَا اَللَّيْلَ وَ تَفَرَّغَ لِلْعِبَادَةِ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2018 - Sama’ah narrated from Abu Basir, from Abu Abdullah (as) who said:\n\"The Messenger of Allah (swt), peace be upon him and his family, when the last ten nights (of Month of Ramadan) arrived, would tighten his waistbelt, avoid women, revive the nights (with worship), and dedicate himself fully to worship.\""
        ]
      }
